	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="/images/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				What I believe is imperative to discuss is how the above island in Erud's Crossing is not, by any means, Kerra Isle. This terminology has been propagated throughout the game and is incorrect. The isle in Erud's crossing is called 'Velious Isle' (the Erudin Port Authority makes this distinction clear, indicating that the ship stops only at Qeynos and on Velious Isle).<BR>
<BR>
Likewise, Kerra Isle is a zone of its own - and an island off the coast of Toxxulia Forest. It is off the western tip of Odus, and is only accessible via the small dock in Toxxulia, swimming, or by the small boat. <BR>
<BR>
Historically, the Erudites bundled up Kerrans and shipped them off to Kerra Isle (the isle off of Toxx, properly named and zoned). I suspect that a group of amiable, pro-Erudite Kerrans founded their settlement in Velious, thus explaining the Kerra Isle lifeforms which inhabit Velious. However, it is utterly erroneous to believe that Kerra Isle is the island in the middle of Erud's Crossing -- and I hope that you all take the lead and the example, and help poor gnomes of Ak'Anon who are trying to find High Priestess Mitty, and send them in the direction of the &quot;right&quot; Kerra Isle.<BR>
<BR>
Best of luck.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
